rComments: This class is so much work, weekly quizzes, midterm, a project. They are all really heavy but end up being worth close to nothing. Also the class is hard to follow and he skips in the explanations all the time O_o
Tricky questions on tests.

His teaching style is incredibly hard to follow. His lecture powerpoint slides are full of text, and his explanations in class are too long! To have effective powerpoint presentations, it's good to only have essential key words... This guys writes novels on every slide!! The information gets lost in the jargon. Hard to follow his notes and lectures
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: The most inspirational professor I had in uOttawa and the best one in the chemical engineering department. When the professor's office hours are "you are welcome at all times" it tells you a lot about how much he's willing to help students. He is funny and explains well to teach heavy material.

The best professor I have met. Even as an international student with poor English and had no knowledge about Laplace transform, I still can easily understand his lectures of process control and finally got A+.
He knows his stuff. But his midterm was horrific.
Best professor that I ever had!
He cares deeply about the success of students, both in plant design and in our professional careers. UOttawa needs more professors like him.
Probably the best Chem Eng prof at Uof0. Tends to go on forever in class without taking a break but conveys the material well. Provides tons of practice problems too.
He Is the Master
The king of chemical engineering. He is extremely knowledgeable and is excellent at sharing this knowledge. No other prof should teach Plant Design, ever. Jules Thibault for president.
He's very humble but he deserves all the praise given to him. Plant design is hard, but he's very supportive of all his students.
One of the best professors in the faculty. Any course taken with him will involve a wonderful learning experience.

Im so sorry for the people who will have Plant design with a prof other than Thibault...  thats all I have to say... So glad that that course is over... now stop reading prof's ratings and go smell a book
Great teach with lots of enthusiasm, fair marking.

He a very knowledgeable person. The courseis tought, but he marks you based on your logics. So dont' think he's beign tough, if you're gettignbad grades, prob cuz you're train of thought had no logics in it. Overall, a very good course where you can learn a lot if you're willing to put the effort into it.
No one better. Know your stuff though.
Good prof. Very nice and caring toward his students. One of the best!
he's extremely nice and knowledgeable; always welcomes questions
Nice guy. Very eager to help. Reasonable tough on the exams, but he bell curves so don't worry too much about the marks you're getting.
Tough class... don't fall behind or ur done!!! Will raise ur final mark after the last exam... Don't worry too much even the dumb-asses pass this course...
Excellent course notes and examples. Amazing prof. Easy on the midterm, extremely tough final. Overall, a very nice and helpful guy who doesn't make you feel stupid.
Really nice guy. Kills on Exams but brings marks up, so that' not bad.

1.  He's always available and eager to help students -always has his door open.  2.Reasonable on the midterm, KILLS on the final. He is a hard marker.  3.  He is a workaholic and is found at school working on weekends
Good teacher and a nice guy... Prepares classes well.
